tip.text: An awesome location for some fine dining. Great ambience, especially during evening time. Try their Slow Cooked Sardinian Style Suckling Pig; love its crispy skin and succulent tasting meat.
If you're looking for some dessert after your meal, Zhao An Granny Grass Jelly will be ideal for you. Simply refreshing, with some toppings of your choice. Try the one with sea coconut. Thumbs up!
Their Fluffy's Chicken Special is yummy! Crispy, spicy, peppery, and delicious. Would definitely recommend this, if you are craving for some finger food or small bites.
If you're into lasagna, try their Pumpkin Lasagna. They serve All-Day breakfast too. Overall, a very nice and soothing ambience during the night, to have a wonderful dinner.
This ramen shop is not known to many, mainly because of its location, situated and hidden in a small corner. But it is quite underrated. Their ramens can be comparable to those better ones out there.
The queue can be quite insane, but their Hokkien Mee makes it worthwhile for queuing up. They use Charcoal as a method to cook, that's why their Mee has that smoky fragrance. Very unique taste.
The Sanji Ramen is surprisingly good, especially the roasted pork shoulder. Its soup base is superb as well.
A wide variety of dishes to choose from, to add to your porridge. It opens till very late night; so if you're hungry in the middle of the night or after clubbing, this is an option for you.
Also try their Grilled Baby Back Ribs, which comes together with mashed potatoes and some broccoli. It can be quite filling, but it really tastes good with its succulent meat and tasty BBQ sauce.
You should try their Fujita Trio; it consists of grilled steak, chicken and spicy garlic and lime shrimp. Definitely tastes delicious!
Great ambience and one of the ideal locations to have breakfast or brunch. Try the Jones Traditional English Breakfast, and add extras if it isn't enough for you!
Prepare a few glasses of iced water, because the Seafood Aglio Olio is gonna spice you up! Shiok!
Try the Cod & Chips; crispy on the outside, tender from the inside!

venue.name: Smiths Authentic British Fish And Chips

tip.text: Mudpies! Can't get enough of it for dessert.
The fermented beancurd is good and "smelly"! Thumbs up!
One of the best ramen restaurants you can find in Singapore. You have to try it to believe it!

formattedAddress: #02-76, The Central (6 Eu Tong Sen St)

tip.text: This McDonald's has been here for decades.
Try the Lor Mee from 新美香. Superb soup base! Add some chilli and vinegar for better taste. There's always a long queue, but it's definitely worth the wait!

venue.name: Old Airport Road Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Although prices are higher than normal hawker food, this is no doubt one of the best places that sells hawker food around this area. Take a stroll along the riverside after your meals; it feels great!
Try the Polpa Di Granchio seafood base pasta. A chef's recommendation. Crabmeat sautéed with garlic. Awesome!
They have a good variety of craft beer selections over here; you'll be spoiled for choice. Nice place to hang out during the evenings.
The food over here is average; price is slightly higher than normal. But if you get a chance to take the outdoor seats, then you can enjoy its beautiful river view of Kallang River.
Might be inconvenient for those who don't drive. But this is no doubt a great place for a healthy breakfast or brunch to kickstart your weekend.
Possibly one of the best Kway Chaps you can find around in SG. The taste of the soup is slightly different from the rest. Definitely worth it. And not forgetting the uncles are friendly too.

venue.name: Lao San Kway Chap 老三棵汁·猪什汤

tip.text: One of the ideal locations to chillout with your dates, especially during night time in a nice weather. Grab a glass of beer, wine or champagne, hang around and enjoy the sea/land breeze.
Free refills of their peppery Bak Kut Teh soup. One of the best you can find within the city. But it can be a little overcrowded with long queues during weekends due to its centralized location.

venue.name: Song Fa Bak Kut Teh 松发肉骨茶

tip.text: Add veges to your Char Kway Teow for a healthier choice! It really tastes better with all the veges together with the dish.
Try the Bacon & Cheese Melt Portobello Mushroom for a starter. Tastes great! Generally you won't be disappointed with their dishes.
The baked Char Siew Bao tastes pretty unique. Overall the Dim Sum are decent and worth your money. The only downside is the long queue. So be prepared to spend at least 30 minutes to queue up.
One of the best places to chillout during any time of the day. This is Starbucks 100th store in Singapore.

formattedAddress: #02-01/02/03 The Fullerton Waterboat House (3 Fullerton Road)

tip.text: They serve a various range of delicious and spicy Peranakan dishes. Don't worry about sweating too much from eating too much spicy food, because it is air-conditioned inside.
Here's one cozy corner in Katong V, where you can chillout with friends and have some tea, coffee and/or dessert. The staffs are friendly too.
GGB Ultimate Breakfast on a sunny Saturday or Sunday morning to kickstart your weekend. Poached egg and crispy bacons! Couldn't be any better than this.
Take a short rest before you carry on with the second half of River Safari. Try one of their Panda Paus! It just looks too cute, and you won't bear to grab a bite on it.

formattedAddress: River Safari, Singapore Zoo (80 Mandai Lake Road)

venue.name: Mama Panda Kitchen 熊猫妈妈小吃

tip.text: Archipelago Battered Fish & Chips is a must-try. It not only comes in big portions, but its taste is superb as well; crispy on the outside, tender on the inside.
The Sashimi that they serve on their dish, comes in big and thick slices. Definitely worth it. And the layout of the place gives you a very Japanese feel.
Come here during evening time, and enjoy the awesome view from Mount Faber. If you are hungry, you can try their Braised Lamb Shank which comes with mashed potatoes; its meat is tender and delicious.
The fried fish soup is delicious, but the waiting time may be a bit long. Try the fried eggs too!

formattedAddress: Luk Lu Eating House (341 Beach Rd.)

tip.text: Easily the best Bak Kut Teh you can possibly find in Singapore. Its peppery soup base leaves you wanting for more servings. Yes it's refillable! And you can brew yourself a pot of Tie Guan Yin tea.

venue.name: Ng Ah Sio Bak Kut Teh

tip.text: No doubt one of the best Bah Kut Tehs around. Its soup base has a herbal-like taste. So if you prefer those peppery-type of Bah Kut Teh, then this may not the one for you.

venue.name: Leong Kee (Klang) Bak Kut Teh 梁记(巴生)肉骨茶

tip.text: Great Japanese food, at premium quality. Shabu-shabu, Salmon Sashimi, Tempura Moriwase, you name it. Their prices ain't that cheap though. But it is worth your money.
Take a seat outdoor, and enjoy the view of Sentosa. And you have to try their pork knuckles! You won't regret!
You won't even know this lovely place exists, unless you keep a lookout while traveling along the main road. A cozy location to chill out at night, with a friend or two, and have some wine together.
With only $3.90, you can make your own Traditional Maccha tea. It's pretty fun and interesting for first-timers. Also try their tasty Tonkotsu Ramen Special.

What else beats having ramen and a nice Sentosa view at the same time. Take the outdoor seats! Miso Chashu Ramen tastes great, with big portions. And the service was good, unlike the negative reviews.
Assorted Sushi Set is awesome. Add a Cold Green Tea Soba if you still have a little room for some more food.

formattedAddress: #B1-12, The Star Vista (1 Vista Exchange Green)

tip.text: 老夫子炒粿條！You just can't go wrong.

venue.name: Old Airport Road Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Try their 滷肉飯, which is one of their signature dishes. It tastes pretty similar to its local Taiwanese version. And the price is decent.

venue.name: 四季 Four Season Taiwanese Cuisine
Old Airport Road Market & Food Centre

tip.text: It's time to workout, with a splendid city view from outside and within. Simply couldn't ask for more!
The Thai Style Kang Kong tastes great, and it is a little spicy. Make sure to get yourselves some iced water.
A large variety of Japanese crusines, from seafood to sushi and desserts. And the best part is that it's a buffet! Free flow! Eat till your heart's content!
An awesome place to chillout; it gives you an amazing vintage feel, with all its Victorian-style decor. Yummy cheesecakes too!
5-Star for the service. Marinated Boneless Beef Ribs -- try it!
"The Titanic" tastes great; their version of Buddha Jumps Over The Wall with fish maw and shark fin melon. Try it!

formattedAddress: #B1-62 Rafffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Rd)

tip.text: If you're craving for spicy food, you can try their Laksa, Curry Chicken or Otah Thick Toast!
P.D Original! Love its sour cream sauce and crispy bacon bits!
The prawns in their Prawn Salad are fresh. And the salad comes with yellow, green and red pepper.
紅燒牛肉麵 -- Its beef meat is tender, and the soup base tastes good. Worth a try!
Holy Grill's Grilled Fish with Cajun Spice just taste simply marvelous! Soft and tender meat, with great-tasting sauce. You will definitely want to come back again for more.

venue.name: Old Airport Road Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Give the Authentic Thai's chicken wings a try!
Having breakfast on a sunny weekend morning never feels this great!

formattedAddress: #01-03, Cintech IV Singapore Science Park I (79 Science Park Dr.)
location.address: #01-03, Cintech IV Singapore Science Park I

tip.text: The Assam Fish is super spicy, but it tastes great!
A truly amazing performance!
Have a cup of Royal Orchid Tea, and enjoy a peaceful afternoon time with the pool view and some sea view.
